window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Can a failed scientist save a city? Can he even save himself?</p> <p>Fired from his dream job and exiled among the misfits and mutants of the Undercity, Tak has gone from wunderkind to washed-out failure in record time. His last hope of reclaiming his life in the shining city above is to somehow prove his wild theories correct.&nbsp;</p> <p>In order to continue his research, Tak accepts a job at a shady underground laboratory, where he struggles to reconcile what he believes to be right with the things he must do to survive. But when a strange plague rips through the people of the Undercity, Tak’s knowledge becomes their only hope of survival. In his race to find a cure, Tak uncovers things about his former life he never knew. Secrets the shining city will work to conceal by any means necessary.</p> <p>With his life on the line, Tak must choose between reclaiming his old life of privilege and saving the Undercity people who need him.</p> <p>Because he can’t have it both ways. And time is running out.</p>"; 
